<div class="container " style="margin-top:60px;">
    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-lg-3" style=" font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif; font-size:1.5em; font-weight:800;background-color: #ffdba9; padding: 30px; text-align: center; background-clip: content-box; padding-top:10px; padding-bottom:50px;">
            <div style="margin:5px 30px;">
                ABOUT
                H2rescueO
            </div>

        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-8" style="font-family: 'Quicksand', sans-serif; font-size:1.1em; font-weight:500;">
            H2rescueO is built to raise awareness about water issues among
            students aged 10-16 in Melbourne by showing information, allowing the
            students to calculate their water consumption and giving them
            recommendations of areas of improvement, displaying tips, games, and
            quizzes along with videos to enable learning and understanding in an
            engaging manner.
        </div>





    </div>

    <div class="row" style="margin-bottom:0px;">

        <div class="col-lg-3" style=" font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif; font-size:1.5em; font-weight:800;background-color: #ffdba9; padding: 30px; text-align: center; background-clip: content-box; padding-top:10px; padding-bottom:0px; ">
            <div style="margin:5px 30px;">
                WHY WE MADE
                H2rescueO
            </div>

        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-8" style="font-family: 'Quicksand', sans-serif; font-size:1.1em; font-weight:500;">
            <p>
                The current water catchment situation in Melbourne as well as in the
                world is deteriorating. The problems regarding water catchments
                include excessive water consumption and water pollution.
            </p>

        </div>




    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-3">

        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-8" style="font-family: 'Quicksand', sans-serif; font-size:1.1em; font-weight:500;">
            <p>
                With respect to water consumption, the increase in water usage and
                water demand is causing the lack of water in the near future in
                Melbourne. In order to protect ourselves from a severe water shortage
                situation, we need to take action now by reducing our consumption and
                raising awareness to the problem at hand.
            </p>
            <p>
                Water pollution in terms of littering, is another growing problem around
                the world as well as in Melbourne.According to the Melbourne Water
                Company, over 3 million dollars has been appropriated for the purpose
                of collecting and removing the waste in order to protect water streams.
            </p>


        </div>


    </div>
